# Memory Game Security Project (Track C)

## Overview

This project implements a simple web-based Memory Game
while demonstrating common web security vulnerabilities
and their secure fixes.

The repository contains two backend implementations:

- Vulnerable version (for attack demonstration)
- Secure version (final protected implementation)

The purpose of this project is to clearly show:

- How common web vulnerabilities are introduced
- How they can be exploited
- How they can be properly mitigated

---

# Tech Stack

- Frontend: HTML, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript
- Backend: Node.js, Express
- Database: SQLite (better-sqlite3)
- Authentication: express-session (cookie-based)

